  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Seeds and Biodiversity, Heritage of the Peoples at the Service of Humankind</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will be implemented in the western region of the state of Santa Catarina, southern Brazil, where there are still many small farmers despite the invasion by monoculture and agribusiness. These practices caused a loss of production system, biodiversity and control over seeds, and has made rural people poorer and driven them out, all while polluting the natural resources. Heifer will support the Small Farmer Movement, or the MPA, to recover, maintain, multiply and distribute 17 varieties or breeds of small-farm biodiversity, through local seeds and animal breeds. The project will also develop alternative marketing channels. It will benefit 150 original rural families and 1,050 more by Passing on the Gift, receiving production resources and training, sharing knowledge, production and genetic resources with the organization, centralization and support of MPA.</narrative>
  </description>
